---
summary: Risk-adjusted swing trading on liquid US large/mid-caps (scored on sortino)
config:
  promotion:
    metric: sortino
---

I want a believable, risk-adjusted record on liquid US large- and mid-cap names — deep
order books, tight spreads, no violent gaps — so backtested fills and the paper record
can be trusted. Hold for a day to a few weeks; avoid strategies that need many intraday
round-trips, because costs and fill realism dominate at that frequency.

Prefer effects with an economic reason to persist: trend continuation after a confirmed
break, pullbacks within an established trend, mean-reversion after overextension on
stable names, post-event drift. Shorting is allowed but optional — take it only when the
downside thesis is as well-formed as a long one, never by default.

Score on Sortino: upside volatility is welcome; downside deviation is what to minimise.
Cut losers on genuine breakdowns rather than hoping. A modest edge that survives
out-of-sample beats a spectacular one that doesn't. Avoid thin, headline-driven, or
recently-listed tickers.
